"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. Maybe getting some rain here in Houston, Texas. I'm a little excited about this development. My garden is looking much, much better. And I wanted to show you something that I just now noticed. I almost stepped on it. Let me re-divert the camera here. So this guy right here, this little black spot. Let me get even closer. This little mound, it looks like an ant pile, but there's no ants in there. It's just ground up dirt. A little pile of it just sitting on the top of the soil there. Those are earthworm castings. There was so much earthworm poop, it had to deposit it on the top of the soil. When uh as we get more rain, you'll see these little piles throughout the yard as you develop fertility. I've been working on my fertility in my backyard for about two years. I have the garden and the worm pile over there. You can see it. And then way in the back behind the chicken tractor is my composting area. And between these three spots, the earthworms have been traveling my yard. And you know, I have been here for five, six years and haven't added any fertilizers or anything like that. So a lot of those are uh dissipating out. Um what you're left with is earthworm castings and soft soil. I walk around my backyard barefoot a lot, and it's almost spongy. It's really nice. Anyway, just wanted to make a video because I'm so excited about earthworm castings, and I can't wait to walk out one day and see like a pile every five feet. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.16,\n      \"end\": 1.36,\n      \"duration\": 1.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.978,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.16,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confid